column14: Please leave your feedback here, we would love to hear from you. Thank you.
This is a very good initiative from our college.

Through the survey that I was able to join in and be a part of what I have come to understand is that a locality that is well managed such as 80 feet road that we went through what would appear normally to be an easily accessible place when actually questioned about their accessibility we understand how almost inconvenient it could be for a disabled person to enter any of these buildings. Most of them are equipped with railing to help with assistance but on my notice there was not a single place that was accessible to people using wheelchairs. On enquiry we understand that them being rental buildings stops the owners from renovating them into accessible mode of entrances. So hopefully we may in one way or other be able to help the regular stores accessible to the disabled.
